    "recipeIngredient": [
        "1 (5-pound) beef brisket",
        "2 tsp. kosher salt ",
        "1 tsp. black pepper",
        "1 Tbsp. canola oil",
        "1 large onion, chopped",
        "2 large carrots, peeled and chopped",
        "3 medium ribs celery, chopped",
        "3 cloves garlic, minced",
        "2 tsp. Italian seasoning",
        "1 cup chicken broth",
        "1/2 cup red wine",
        "1 Tbsp. soy sauce",
        "1 bay leaf",
        "1/4 cup cold water",
        "1 1/2 Tbsp. cornstarch"
    ],
    "recipeInstructions": [
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/GZ7WzxR-hydqvI9IrjwoFug6BoQ=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Southern-Living-Crockpot_Brisket_001-6f906492a5054c77b1186c837c1480e8.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Gather your ingredients: Make sure you have all your ingredients ready to cook."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/M47EzGEvvN94ACQlhktoGuLAoXw=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Southern-Living-Crockpot_Brisket_002-c11334ffd977403a995623281d86ca0b.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Prepare brisket: Pat brisket dry and season with salt and pepper. "
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/gje0vg3AsPoRdEgAf8pGXy9jXXc=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Southern-Living-Crockpot_Brisket_004-5eef338de46e49fd81c914bf24f06533.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Brown the brisket: Heat a large Dutch oven or skillet over medium-high heat. Add the oil to coat the pan. Sear the meat until a deep brown, about 5 minutes per side. Remove from the pan. "
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/MaJcjmhc_JY18ard0F5mVMJxdT0=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Southern-Living-Crockpot_Brisket_007-7d7396f8d554484588e90f2ea53c6555.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Saute vegetables: Reduce the heat to medium, and add the onions, carrots, and celery. Cook until soft, about 5 minutes. Stir in the garlic and Italian seasoning and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Remove from heat."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/DzlbU1fh5L1dz1rET2MY4iddtSQ=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Southern-Living-Crockpot_Brisket_011-fd21ae25975c40d3bb0782b2a3e5402f.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Add ingredients to slow cooker: Add the broth, red wine, soy sauce, and bay leaf to an 8-qt. slow cooker; stir to combine. Nestle the meat into the sauce, fat-side down. Top with the vegetables. Cover and cook on LOW for 8 hours or until fork tender."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/8BYlzNHEH5PO4HsA5iw4HeLld5o=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Southern-Living-Brisket_098-fa97a9b7e40c4848aab2c5cf25478439.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Slice or shred brisket: Remove the brisket to a cutting board and let rest for 10 minutes. Slice against the grain or shred with two forks."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/IdtRApgr2IJF15CNjaelsGpXjnQ=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Southern-Living-Brisket_111-09fb706b730d4704b20507168236b18d.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Make sauce: Strain the sauce through a fine mesh strainer into a medium saucepan. Press the vegetables with a wooden spoon to extract any remaining juices and discard solids. Skim the surface of fat. Simmer the sauce over medium-high heat for 5 minutes."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/-yQ0hqFXccnJvFpx-aSKuy5fYp8=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Southern-Living-Brisket_134-563c0f6488374f2cba9d18425ba73063.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Thicken sauce: In a small bowl, whisk together 1/4 cup cold water and cornstarch. Whisk the cornstarch slurry into the sauce and cook until thickened, 1 to 2 minutes. Season to taste with additional salt and pepper, if needed. Serve the sauce over the brisket."
        }
    ],
